manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Here's Why Dead Sea Mud is a unique and exceptional component in beauty care. Dead Sea mud contains 21 minerals and is one of the most mineral-rich mud on earth. It includes key skin-nourishing minerals such as sodium, magnesium, calcium, bromide, potassium, iron, sulfur, silicon dioxide and much more. Dead Sea Mud is known to have many soothing and calming properties that can help improve the skin appearance and relieve irritated skin at the same time. For this reason it is one of the most sought-after skin care addition.

Previous page Glowing Skin Dead Sea Mud provides the necessary hydration to the skin to help promote more radiant looking skin. Clean Skin Dead Sea Mud is known to gently exfoliate the skin, drawing out excess oil which helps unclog pores. Smooth Skin Dead Sea Mud helps naturally enhance skin elasticity and improve the appearance of skin blemishes. Calm Skin Dead Sea Mud is renowned for its soothing properties and its ability to help relieve dry itchy skin. Next page 1 Glowing Skin 2 Clean Skin 3 Smooth Skin 4 Calm Skin

How often can I use Dead Sea Mud Mask? It is recommended to use Dead Sea Mud Mask twice per week. How do I apply Dead Sea Mud Mask? Cleanse skin thoroughly before applying the mask. Apply a thin layer to face avoiding eyes and lips. Leave mask on for 10 minutes until it dries. Use warm water to gently remove and pat dry with a clean cloth. Recommended to follow with a moisturizer Does this work for all skin types? Dead Sea Mud is considered safe for all skin types. However, it is important to do a patch test on a small part of the skin area prior to first use. Wait several minutes to observe. Discontinue if irritation occurs or if you suspect a reaction. Does it sting? A slight burning sensation is normal while the mask is drying out on the skin as this means that the mask is working on cleaning the skin. However, if it becomes too much, wash it off for instant relief. How does Dead Sea Mud work on the skin? As the Dead Sea Mud dries on the skin, it absorbs dead skin cells, impurities and excess oils which helps unclog pores and cleanse the skin. The dirt and impurities are washed away together with the mask, leaving the skin feeling fresher and cleaner.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good without irritation
reviews.reviewText: There is no uncomfortable tightness during the process of applying the mask. It has a light aroma, not the cheap perfume smell. It is very comfortable overall. reviews.reviewText: I love this mask. I try to use it once a week, and when I do, my skin feels so clean and smooth. Takes a little bit to dry, but results are fantastic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I have very sensitive skin and large pores
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the Dead Sea Mud Mask. So far I have used it 4 times. I like that it doesn’t leave my skin red. I have bought more expensive products that irritate my skin. Although the product says it is for oily and acne prone skin, I do not have that problem. I think that is why it felt like it dried out my skin a little. I recently started using an oil or moisturizer immediately after I remove it. While it does leave my skin feeling softer, I still don’t know if its doing much of anything else (that is why I gave it fours stars). But I will be buying another one of their masks for my mom since she struggles with products for her sensitive skin too.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A quick trip to the spa
reviews.reviewText: This product is so satisfying to use. After applying it and washing it you'll feel like a baby again. It is therapeutic and you feel as though your skin is clean and can breathe. Save yourself the trip to the spa and go with this face mask instead!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I recently tried this Dead Sea mud mask, and I have to say, I'm really impressed. The first thing I noticed was how silky and smooth the texture of the mask was. It was easy to apply, and it went on smoothly without any clumps or bumps.After letting the mask sit for a few minutes, I could feel it working its magic. It started to tighten and dry on my skin, and I could feel a slight tingling sensation. While it was drying, I could see the impurities being drawn out of my skin, and my pores looked visibly smaller after I washed the mask off. My skin felt refreshed and revitalized after using it, and I was left with a smooth, glowing complexion.Another thing I appreciated about this mud mask was that it didn't leave my skin feeling dry or tight, like some other masks can. Instead, it left my skin feeling soft and hydrated, which is a rare treat for me. I've used this mask several times now, and I've noticed that it helps to reduce the appearance of blemishes and fine lines as well.Overall, I'm really happy with this Dead Sea mud mask, and I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for an effective, yet gentle skincare treatment. It's a great way to pamper your skin and give it the nourishment it needs to look its best.
